  "prompt": "Does it hurt to get stitches removed?",
  "response": "The sensation of having stitches removed can vary from person to person, but it is generally not considered painful. Most people report feeling a mild tugging or pulling sensation as the stitches are taken out. The process is usually quick, and any discomfort is minimal and brief. However, individual experiences can vary based on factors such as the location of the stitches, the type of stitches used, and personal pain tolerance. If you have any concerns or experience significant discomfort, it\u2019s always a good idea to discuss them with your healthcare provider.",
